# Heritage: version must appear in commit messages

The user controls when versions change; see **heritage-version-manual**. When a commit includes changes **they** made to **any** of the following, the **commit message must explicitly state the Heritage app version** (e.g. `v1.2.8` in the subject or first line of the body):

- [`heritage/service-worker.js`](heritage/service-worker.js) — `VERSION` constant (and derived cache names)
- [`heritage/manifest.json`](heritage/manifest.json) — `version` field
- [`heritage/js/app.js`](heritage/js/app.js) — `APP_VERSION`
- [`heritage/index.html`](heritage/index.html) — `?v=` cache-bust query strings on CSS/JS assets

**Examples (good):**

- `heritage 1.2.8: fix IndexedDB boot on Windows PWA`
- `heritage v1.3.0: search modal, README updates`

**Avoid:** commits that touch those version surfaces without naming the version in the message.

When bumping for a release, the user typically runs `heritage/version.ps1` so service worker, manifest, `app.js`, and `index.html` stay aligned; mirror that single version in the commit message.
